		{
			dependencies: ["1B935334CB080110"]
			description: [
				"Early in the game, ore processing is a bit different than in other experiences, but don't worry because it is easily automatable even in the early game."
				""
				"To process ores, you need to follow these steps"
				""
				"&e-&r 1: crush the raw ore in a &5Pestle and mortar&r to obtain the crushed version of it"
				"&e-&r 2: heat the crushed in a &5Seared melter&r."
				"&e-&r 3: solidify the molten fluid into bars, slabs, or any other mold you want"
				""
				"You can check out an early game ore processing automation setup in the modpack Guide at &9Setups -> First Ore Processing&r"
				""
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"To build your first melter, place the Seared melter above the &9Seared heater&r or&9 Seared tank&r"
				""
				"&e-&r to pour the molten fluid into casts, use faucets"
				"&e-&r For a smelter to work, fuel is needed, if you use the Seared heater use any item fuel, for the Seared tank use any fluid fuel"
				"&e-&r you can automate the input of items into the melter using funnels, and the output using a redstone signal in the faucet"
				""
				"&a⚠ Tip:&r  EMI (or JEI) shows which are the possible fuels that can be used for melting"
				""
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Automating pestle and mortar is very easy"
				""
				"&e-&r You can insert or extract items using hopper"
				""
				"&c⚠ Alert:&r Be careful when automating certain recipes with pestle and mortar because if any additional item is added to the inputs it pauses the recipe"
			]
			icon: "tconstruct:seared_melter"
			id: "07FFBA74160FAE8B"
			rewards: [{
				id: "379B61423BE96302"
				item: "kubejs:common_techbuck"
